ounsel to management and others based on industry and professional best practices. A proficiency in using Microsoft Word, Microsoft PowerPoint, Microsoft Excel, and MS Outlook. Hiring Preferences Experience in complex, highly regulated industries and/or health care Ability to work in a high-paced, high volume environment with changing priorities. Demonstrated skills in communications program management and team leadership. Superior oral and written communication skills are essential. Demonstrated ability to analyze key program issues and recommend appropriate messaging and communication vehicles. Solid media relations experience Proven capability for crisis and issues management. The candidate must have the ability to be a hands-on manager of multiple projects and/or campaigns. Strong project management skills. Excellent planning, interpersonal, problem-solving and leadership skills are necessary to be successful in this position. Strong knowledge of and experience with all communications vehicles and technology, including written, Web, video, broadcast, and social media Ability to tie departmental and project objectives to overall corporate goals. Meeting facilitation skills ",
